  <summary>10/30/2001--Introduced.
Military Widows Equity Act - Repeals, as of October 1, 2002, certain provisions which require the offset of amounts paid in dependency and indemnity compensation from Survivor Benefit Plan (SBP) annuities for the surviving spouses of former military personnel who are entitled to military pay or who would be entitled to retired pay except for being under 60 years of age.Provides for the recoupment of certain amounts previously paid to SBP recipients in the form of a retired pay refund.</summary>
</bill>
